The two types of schema are different in terms of output content. In the graphql format, only deprecation_reason is output.

Therefore, we will use JSON format schema for this documentation.

## Output documentation

[@2fd/graphdoc](https://github.com/2fd/graphdoc).

```zsh
$ npm install @2fd/graphdoc
$ graphdoc -s schema.json -o docs/ 
```

The HTML file will be extracted under docs/. The HTML file is a little difficult to handle as it is, so we will make it available in Pages. (as usual).

<details>
<summary>.github/workflows/doc.yml</summary>

```yml
name: doc

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main


jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
    - uses: actions/checkout@v2
    - uses: actions/setup-python@v3
      with:
        python-version: '3.10'
        cache: 'pip'
        cache-dependency-path: 'requirements.dev.txt'
    - uses: actions/setup-node@v2
      with:
        node-version: '16'
    - name: npm install
      run: |
        npm install -g @2fd/graphdoc
    - name: pip install
      run: |
        pip install -r requirements.txt
    - name: git init
      run: |
        git config --global user.name "${GITHUB_ACTOR}"
        git config --global user.email "${GITHUB_ACTOR}@users.noreply.github.com"
        git remote set-url origin https://x-access-token:${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}@github.com/$GITHUB_REPOSITORY
    - name: generate document
      run: |
        graphdoc -s schema.json -o docs/ 
    - uses: peaceiris/actions-gh-pages@v3
      with:
        github_token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
        publish_dir: ./docs
    - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v3
      with:
        name: schema
        path: |
          schema.json
          schema.graphql
```
</details>

- - - 

In the case of GitLab, unlike the way GitHub Pages is published, you can specify a directory inside CI and it will deploy automatically, but in the case of GitHub, you need to put the HTML in `docs/` or root dir on the branch.

In this case, it is very convenient to use `peaceiris/actions- gh- pages@v3 ` to automatically push the specified directory to the `gh- pages` branch and deploy it.

